notes.note: Laird had a tough start to the game as Aish tagged him but he worked through it and ended with 28 touches at 78%. Interestingly he did spend a lot of time on the bench playing just 77% of the game on ground.
Laird had 18 contested touches amongst his 26 and he also led the game in clearances with 11 which was a great score against a team he has had issues with scoring against in the past.
Laird was brilliant and it was the Laird we expected to see. 39 touches with 15 contested and an equal game high 7 clearances.

Laird had one of his quietest games for a long time against the Giants with just 18 possessions which is far short of his average of 33 from last year.   He normally has big tackle numbers but had just 3 this week (the highest in the game was only 4).
If you can afford to fit Laird in your side he is a perma-captain for you.

Michaelanney was given the role on Bolton for the game and he was good. Being given this role would lead us to think that his job security is very good so just keep him there on your bench.
Michaelanney was promoted as a lock down defender but he did end the game with 12 touches at 91% efficiency doing the job on Riccardi. He could be a popular trade in for a failed rookie.

notes.note: Rankine has now posted two over 110 in the last two weeks and those scores have come with goals. 4 last week and 3 this week. His value will certainly rise if you want to ride the wave of a small forward.
Rankine had 17 touches and used the footy well going at 88%. His score does include 4 goals at key points in the game but his role is to kick clutch goals so don't discount them from his score.

15 of Ashcroft's 31 touches were contested and he had 9 clearances which was an equal high with Dunkley for the game. The only downfall to his scoring is his disposal efficiency which was low for the second week in a row.
The young Lion showed us glimpses in the loss to the Power with a goal and 13 possessions. But his efficiency was well down which hurt his scoring. Don't panic on him as he is just warming up.
Ashcroft is a must have for all Supercoaches. He was fantastic in the pre-season with 26 touches at 80% against the Cats.

Cripps top scored for the Blues with 15 of his 25 touches contested. This was the great form we saw from him last season and he has just carried it forward.
